answers.answer: Hello SRA,This forum focuses on Juvenile Diabetes issues and we are all volunteers, unlike the other MedHelp forums which, I understand, are staffed by medical professionals.As a layperson reading your msg, I would suggest that you discuss the results with your doctor, and if the topic is at all serious or there are options for treatments, then ask for a recommendation for another doctor to give you a second opinion.Perhaps you can find a MedHelp forum that discusses your underlying condition.  Good luck, tho', it seems tougher to get back serious test results during the holiday.

question: I TOKE AN MRI, THE RESULTS WERE I HAD BILATERAL OCCULSION.I LATER HAD AN ARERIOGRAM PERFORMED WHICH CAME BACK WIDE AND PATENT. SHOULD I LOOK INTO THIS FURTHER OR ACCEPT THE RESULTS OF THE LATTER TEST?
title: ARTERIOGRAM/MRI RESULTS
